{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-06-04-1",
 "title": "A Short Interview by the Fountain",
 "summary": "Returning to Plaxton City's Fountain Square to wrap up a story, the IGNews reporter Loy Marin spots the disguised NRI agent Bazil McKenzie (as Mege Vauki) and, nagged by a half-formed memory of the man, stops him for a brief interview about Caspar's politics. Bazil, uneasy under the gaze of Loy's camera droid, gives guarded answers about the system's prized independence and self-sufficiency while claiming to be a Tatooine-born trader. Eva Sargent jogs through the square unrecognized, pausing to splash fountain water on her face, while the marine Ernie Pallando and a cloaked passerby named Jairen drift through. The inconclusive interview satisfies neither Loy's curiosity nor his story, and as the square empties Bazil lingers alone beneath a streetlamp, gazing at the stars and whispering of his lost love Casey before slipping back toward his ship.",
